  <!-- Page Header -->
  <header class="page-header">
    <div class="page-header-inner">
      <span class="ph-eyebrow">Academic Background</span>
      <h1>Education</h1>
      <p class="ph-subtitle">Government of India sponsored PhD scholar with a research career spanning NLP, probabilistic modelling and applied AI.</p>
      <div class="page-header-stats">
        <div class="ph-stat"><span class="ph-num">1</span><span class="ph-label">PhD</span></div>
        <div class="ph-stat"><span class="ph-num">1</span><span class="ph-label">Postgrad</span></div>
        <div class="ph-stat"><span class="ph-num">1</span><span class="ph-label">Undergrad</span></div>
        <div class="ph-stat"><span class="ph-num">£100k+</span><span class="ph-label">PhD Funding</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="main-container">
    <section class="fade-in">
      <h2><i class="fas fa-graduation-cap"></i> Academic Qualifications</h2>
      
      <div class="edu-timeline">
        <div class="degree-card" id="phd">
          <div class="edu-pin"><i class="fas fa-database"></i></div>
          <div class="degree-header">
            <h3>PhD, Computer Science</h3>
            <span class="edu-meta">
              <i class="fas fa-university"></i> Queen's University Belfast, UK
              <span class="edu-date"><i class="fas fa-calendar"></i> Oct 2019 – Dec 2024</span>
            </span>
          </div>
          <div class="edu-thesis-callout">
            <span class="thesis-label"><i class="fas fa-quote-left"></i> Thesis</span>
            <span class="thesis-title">Evidence-Based Approach to Verification of Online Health-Related Content</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="edu-bullets">
            <li>Government of India sponsored QUB–Tezpur University Collaborative PhD Programme scholar.</li>
            <li>Developed an automated pipeline for verifying online health information using transformer models (BERT, SBERT).</li>
            <li>Specialized in unsupervised algorithms for data-scarce settings, enabling verification with minimal labeled data.</li>
            <li>Implemented custom NLP modules with Huggingface, NLTK, spaCy, and scispaCy.</li>
            <li>Published research in peer-reviewed journals and conferences (see <a href="papers.html">Papers</a> tab).</li>
            <li>Open-sourced fine-tuned models on HuggingFace for public use.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="edu-funding-badge"><i class="fas fa-award"></i> £100,000+ Govt of India scholarship (tuition, accommodation, subsistence, conference support)</div>
          <div class="edu-tags">
            <span class="edu-tag"><i class="fas fa-brain"></i> BERT</span>
            <span class="edu-tag"><i class="fas fa-brain"></i> SBERT</span>
            <span class="edu-tag"><i class="fab fa-python"></i> HuggingFace</span>
            <span class="edu-tag"><i class="fas fa-language"></i> NLTK</span>
            <span class="edu-tag"><i class="fas fa-language"></i> spaCy</span>
            <span class="edu-tag"><i class="fas fa-flask"></i> scispaCy</span>
            <span class="edu-tag"><i class="fas fa-search"></i> Weak Supervision</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="degree-card" id="mtech">
          <div class="edu-pin"><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i></div>
          <div class="degree-header">
            <h3>MTech, Information Technology</h3>
            <span class="edu-meta">
              <i class="fas fa-university"></i> Tezpur University, Assam, India
              <span class="edu-date"><i class="fas fa-calendar"></i> Jun 2014 – Jul 2016</span>
            </span>
          </div>
          <ul class="edu-bullets">
            <li><strong>Dissertation:</strong> Probabilistic Modeling of Language Competition and Extinction</li>
            <li>Developed a probabilistic model to study the dynamics between coexisting and endangered languages.</li>
            <li>Extended the model with Markov Chain analysis to predict language fate under various scenarios.</li>
            <li>Designed and ran experiments using Matlab; interpreted results to support language preservation research.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="edu-tags">
            <span class="edu-tag"><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> Probabilistic Models</span>
            <span class="edu-tag"><i class="fas fa-project-diagram"></i> Markov Chains</span>
            <span class="edu-tag"><i class="fas fa-calculator"></i> Matlab</span>
            <span class="edu-tag"><i class="fas fa-language"></i> Language Modelling</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="degree-card" id="be">
          <div class="edu-pin"><i class="fas fa-code"></i></div>
          <div class="degree-header">
            <h3>BE, Computer Science &amp; Engineering</h3>
            <span class="edu-meta">
              <i class="fas fa-university"></i> Gauhati University, Assam, India
              <span class="edu-date"><i class="fas fa-calendar"></i> Jun 2009 – Jul 2013</span>
            </span>
          </div>
          <ul class="edu-bullets">
            <li><strong>Major Project:</strong> Android Notepad Application with Reminder and To-Do Features (Java)</li>
            <li>Completed comprehensive coursework in algorithms, data structures, and programming languages (C, C++, Java).</li>
            <li>Engaged in practical learning through coding assignments, projects, and team collaborations.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="edu-tags">
            <span class="edu-tag"><i class="fab fa-java"></i> Java</span>
            <span class="edu-tag"><i class="fab fa-android"></i> Android</span>
            <span class="edu-tag"><i class="fab fa-cuttlefish"></i> C/C++</span>
            <span class="edu-tag"><i class="fas fa-project-diagram"></i> Data Structures</span>
            <span class="edu-tag"><i class="fas fa-calculator"></i> Algorithms</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
